        <div class="manage-innovation">
            <h2>Major Activities under Umang</h2>
            <div class="innovation-point">
                <div class="innovate flex-reverse" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration="3500">
                    <div class="innovate-photo"><img src="/Content/images/activities/activity-1.png" alt="Activity 1"></div>
                    <div class="innovate-content">
                        <p><b>Rollout of Modular Sessions:</b></p>
                        <p>
                            For imparting knowledge, skills and confidence among SHG
                            members, Umang team designed 21 modular sessions for SHGs covering topics such as
                            ill-effects of child marriage, importance of girls’ education, child rights and
                            entitlements, mother-daughter communication, etc. PCI India trained Active Women (cadre
                            of frontline workers), who conducted the sessions during SHG meetings (one out of every
                            4 weekly sessions were devoted to Umang modules). Similarly, separate modules were
                            developed for VOs (21 modules) and CLFs (14).
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="innovate" data-aos="fade-left" data-aos-duration="3500">
                    <div class="innovate-content">
                        <p><b>Community Level Campaigns:</b></p>
                        <p>
                            Mother Daughter event was an integral part of Umang that
                            highlighted the power of mother-daughter bond in resolving issues and shifting
                            regressive social norms (such as child marriage).
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="innovate-photo"><img src="/Content/images/activities/activity-2.png" alt="Activity 2"></div>
                </div>
                <div class="innovate flex-reverse" data-aos="fade-right" data-aos-duration="3500">
                    <div class="innovate-photo"><img src="/Content/images/activities/activity-3.png" alt="Activity 3"></div>
                    <div class="innovate-content">
                        <p><b>Kishori Help Desk:</b></p>
                        <p>
                            To fill the gap between aspirations & reality among adolescent girls
                            for their education & career, Kishori (meaning adolescent) Help Desks were created
                            towards the end of 2022. Set up at CLF offices and managed by trained counsellors, these
                            help desks offer counselling to adolescent girls & their parents on education, career,
                            life skills & SRHR. Career counselling was provided to girls based on their psychometric
                            tests that help identify their acumen for selecting suitable career options and study
                            streams. Since it came late, the uptake has been low and yet to cover adequate number of
                            girls at the time of endline survey.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="innovate" data-aos="fade-left" data-aos-duration="3500">
                    <div class="innovate-content">
                        <p><b>Enhancing Leadership & Advocacy Skills of CLF Members:</b></p>
                        <p>
                            To enable women leaders take
                            ownership for addressing social issue, the project has facilitated engagement with Block
                            Level Child Protection Committee (BLCPC) in Nala where CLF & SAC leaders raised their
                            concerns regarding quality services for adolescent girls to continue their education and
                            thus avoid child/early marriages.
                        </p>
                    </div>
